Installation 
--------------
- uncompress the tarball suitably on your CE
- move to jobview folder
- set BASEDIR in setup.sh correctly
- now edit lib/Collector/config.pl
  . set baseDir [this might be automated in future]
  . site, domain, lrms_version (not used yet)
  [
    . acctDir 
    . jobDir
  ] 
  . set supportedGroups array

- edit bin/overview.sh. In the example file we scp the html and images to the web server document area. 
  Your choice might be different. The basic steps are:

  - on the (apache) web server 
   . mkdir -p /var/www/html/pbs/images
  - scp -r html/css YOUR_WEBSERVER:/var/www/html/pbs/
  - scp -r html/js YOUR_WEBSERVER:/var/www/html/pbs/

You will further need to install a few Perl modules, namely

perl-Template-Alloy
perl-rrdtool

You should be all set now.
cd bin/
./create_rrd.sh
./overview.sh

This will create html/overview.html and images/rrd/*.gif
which will be copied over to the web server, provided you
set the paths correctly. If things go fine, you should be able
to see the page. Do

cp overview.cron /etc/cron.d # after checking that the path is correct
service crond restart
touch /etc/crontab

